Pre-Game Insights: Babar Azam-led Pakistan cricket team will face England in their last league stage match at Eden Gardens International Cricket Stadium, Kolkata.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan needs to beat England by 287 runs while batting first or 284 balls to spare while chasing to keep their journey alive in the ICC World Cup.
Others: Babar Azam has scored 282 runs with an average of around 40 in 8 matches this World Cup season.
